\n< Serena >The water isn't as murky as I thought. Maybe it's
the effect of the slime.

\n< Serena >It's true that we might be able to live here if we
just live. However, what are we going to do about
dealing with the slime...?

\n< Serena >Mmm... I can't see any coherence in the structure.
Did they expand the city haphazardly without any
planning?

\n< Serena >...No, that's not it. Maybe they're repurposing
old ruins.

\n< Serena >This scale of sewer system is not even found in
the capital city. It's not something that can be
equipped with the budget of just one city.

\n< Serena >I see, I see. So, the parts that are not suitable
for sewage are being balanced out by keeping
slimes, huh?

\n< Serena >...This is bad. I came here to apprehend
criminals. If I'm just sightseeing, I'll be caught
off guard.
\n< Serena >...Huh!?
\n< Serena >You! What are you doing there!
\n< ？？？ >W-Why are there people here?!
\n< Serena >Get over there!
\n< Serena >What a fast escape! Is that person a ninja!?
\n< Serena >I won't let you escape!
\n< Serena >Hmm...

\n< Serena >It's probably because we're underground... It
feels so cold.

\n< Serena >But it's not as smelly as I thought. Could it be
because the slimes are decomposing all the waste?

\n< Serena >It's definitely not a pleasant environment. Let's
quickly find this Gee thing and get out of here.
